# Software Architecture

## Next.js App Router

This project uses Next.js 16 with the App Router. Key principles:

- **Server Components by default** - Components are server-rendered unless marked with `"use client"`
- **File-based routing** - Routes defined by the file system under `frontend/app/`
- **API Route Handlers** - Backend endpoints in `frontend/app/api/*/route.ts`
- **Layouts and Templates** - Shared UI in `layout.tsx` files

## Directory Structure

```
frontend/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router
│   ├── api/               # API route handlers
│   ├── layout.tsx         # Root layout
│   ├── page.tsx           # Landing page
│   ├── global-error.tsx   # Global error boundary
│   ├── not-found.tsx      # 404 page
│   └── globals.css        # Global styles
├── components/            # Shared components
│   └── ui/               # UI primitives
├── lib/                   # Utilities
│   └── utils.ts          # Helper functions
├── hooks/                 # Custom React hooks
└── styles/                # Global styles
```

### Where Things Go

| What | Where |
| --- | --- |
| Pages and layouts | `frontend/app/` |
| API route handlers | `frontend/app/api/` |
| UI primitives | `frontend/components/ui/` |
| Shared components/sections | `frontend/components/` |
| Custom hooks | `frontend/hooks/` |
| Utility functions | `frontend/lib/` |
| Unit tests | Co-located with source files |
| E2E tests | `frontend/e2e/` |

## Data Fetching Patterns

### Server Components (Default)

Use for data that doesn't need client interactivity:

```typescript
// app/page.tsx - Server Component (no "use client")
export default async function HomePage() {
  return <LandingPage />;
}
```

### API Routes for Form Submissions

Handle form submissions and external integrations through Next.js API routes:

```typescript
// app/api/contact/route.ts
export async function POST(request: Request) {
  const body = await request.json();
  // Validate with Zod, process, send notifications
  return Response.json({ success: true });
}
```

### When to Use What

| Pattern | Use When |
| --- | --- |
| Server Component | Static content, page sections |
| Client Component | Interactive UI, forms, state |
| API Route | Form submissions, external integrations |

## Component Patterns

### Server vs Client Components

```typescript
// Server Component (default) - no directive needed
export default function HeroSection() {
  return <section>...</section>;
}

// Client Component - needs interactivity
"use client";
export default function ContactForm() {
  const [submitted, setSubmitted] = useState(false);
  return <form onSubmit={...}>...</form>;
}
```

### Animation (GSAP + Lenis)

This project uses GSAP for animations and Lenis for smooth scroll. Both require client components:

```typescript
"use client";
import { useEffect, useRef } from "react";
import gsap from "gsap";

export default function AnimatedSection() {
  const ref = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null);
  useEffect(() => {
    gsap.from(ref.current, { opacity: 0, y: 40, duration: 0.8 });
  }, []);
  return <div ref={ref}>...</div>;
}
```

## Naming Conventions

### Files

| Element | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component files | `PascalCase` | `NutritionSection.tsx` |
| Utility files | `kebab-case` | `form-utils.ts` |
| Hook files | `camelCase` | `useContactForm.ts` |
| Test files | `*.test.ts` | `utils.test.ts` |
| E2E test files | `*.spec.ts` | `home.spec.ts` |

### Code

| Element | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Functions/methods | `camelCase` | `submitContact` |
| Components | `PascalCase` | `NutritionSection` |
| Variables | `camelCase` | `formData` |
| Types/Interfaces | `PascalCase` | `ContactForm` |
| Constants | `UPPER_SNAKE` | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |

## Anti-Patterns

### Don't Put Business Logic in Components

```typescript
// BAD - Logic mixed into component
function ContactForm() {
  const [data, setData] = useState({});
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/api/contact").then(res => res.json()).then(setData);
  }, []);
  return <form>...</form>;
}

// GOOD - Logic in hook, component just renders
function ContactForm() {
  const { submit, isLoading } = useContactForm();
  return <form onSubmit={submit}>...</form>;
}
```

### Don't Catch Errors Unless You Can Recover

```typescript
// BAD - Swallowing the error
async function fetchData() {
  try {
    const res = await fetch("/api/data");
    return res.json();
  } catch (error) {
    console.log("Error fetching data");
    return null; // Swallowed!
  }
}

// GOOD - Let Next.js error boundaries handle it
async function fetchData() {
  const res = await fetch("/api/data");
  if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`API error: ${res.status}`);
  return res.json();
}
```

### Don't Create Abstractions for Single Use Cases

```typescript
// BAD - Unnecessary abstraction
class APIClient {
  async post(url: string, body: unknown) { /* ... */ }
}

// GOOD - Direct implementation
async function submitContact(data: ContactForm) {
  const res = await fetch("/api/contact", {
    method: "POST",
    body: JSON.stringify(data),
  });
  return res.json();
}
```

## UI/UX

- **Tailwind CSS** for all styling: no CSS modules, no styled-components
- **GSAP** for animations: scroll-triggered reveals, transitions
- **Lenis** for smooth scroll
- **Mobile-first** responsive design
